Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.57,0:00:09.11,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.11,0:00:13.82,Main,,0,0,0,,You wish to withdraw your investment\Nin the research in question?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.82,0:00:16.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I heard a strange rumor recently--
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.74,0:00:19.41,Main,,0,0,0,,that Dr. Hayase has gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.41,0:00:20.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.91,0:00:24.37,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on with his matter transporter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.58,0:00:27.08,Main,,0,0,0,,It's proceeding apace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.75,0:00:32.01,Main,,0,0,0,,But we haven't had any progress reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.01,0:00:34.43,Main,,0,0,0,,This violates our contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.39,0:00:39.60,Main,,0,0,0,,You'll just have to trust me, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.19,0:00:48.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Very well. I'll wait a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.48,0:00:50.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.32,0:00:52.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Yamamuro is leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.87,0:01:08.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Regarding the Hayase laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.25,0:01:12.42,Main,,0,0,0,,we have identified a researcher we\Nbelieve was involved in his core research.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.55,0:01:14.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.68,0:02:48.85,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 3\NFranklin's Spirit of Defiance"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.85,0:02:51.65,Main,,0,0,0,,"Well done is better than well said."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:57.15,Main,,0,0,0,,"Supplementary Lesson"\NThis was famously said by Benjamin Franklin.\NHayase, can you translate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.15,0:02:57.53,Main,,0,0,0,,This was famously said by Benjamin Franklin.\NHayase, can you translate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.94,0:03:00.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.07,0:03:03.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, give me just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.83,0:03:07.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Get your supplementary lesson done ASAP!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.16,0:03:10.87,Main,,0,0,0,,We're meeting at the lab\Nto continue our search!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:13.75,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't do this "ASAP"!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.71,0:03:17.67,Main,,0,0,0,,I hate English!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.67,0:03:21.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Hmm. It seems to be\Ntaking you some time, Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.55,0:03:23.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay. Ichikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.51,0:03:26.93,Main,,0,0,0,,It means that actions\Nspeak louder than words!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:30.60,Main,,0,0,0,,That answer is correct, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.11,0:03:36.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, this is just...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.69,0:03:41.11,Main,,0,0,0,,This is not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:43.78,Main,,0,0,0,,"This is not fair."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:50.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, I think it's best to get your\Nlanguage translated in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.41,0:03:53.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Real time translation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:56.46,Main,,0,0,0,,You do speak fluent English.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.46,0:04:00.30,Main,,0,0,0,,But that's no reason not to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.30,0:04:01.59,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm confiscating this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.59,0:04:04.22,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, Mr. Sato! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.22,0:04:06.97,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't just go straight to the red card!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.19,0:04:17.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Mizuki! You're home already?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.06,0:04:17.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Listen to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.90,0:04:21.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Ugh, Mom's home already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:23.90,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm late! I'm late! I'm super late!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:25.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:26.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.87,0:04:27.74,Main,,0,0,0,,You're coming too, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.74,0:04:28.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.92,0:04:38.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Good day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.96,0:04:40.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome to our tea party.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:42.97,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.76,0:04:47.01,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you think? Does it suit me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.01,0:04:49.60,Main,,0,0,0,,You called us here for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:50.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.27,0:04:54.39,Main,,0,0,0,,That's amazing, Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.39,0:04:57.31,Main,,0,0,0,,That dress looks so good on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.31,0:04:58.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:04.28,Main,,0,0,0,,And these madelines and\Nbiscottis look really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.28,0:05:07.45,Main,,0,0,0,,But the cute tea set is the best part!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:11.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Isn't that Mom's antique tea set?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.45,0:05:14.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Erk! Wh-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.91,0:05:17.42,Main,,0,0,0,,I just saw it looking lonely\Nin the back of the cupboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:20.96,Main,,0,0,0,,and decided to help the poor thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:22.80,Main,,0,0,0,,That's my Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:25.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I bet the tea set must be so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.97,0:05:28.30,Main,,0,0,0,,I hear good actions are the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.30,0:05:30.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.10,0:05:33.31,Main,,0,0,0,,It's something we learned in\Nour supplementary lesson today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.31,0:05:35.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right. My notes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.98,0:05:37.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.48,0:05:38.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Where are my notes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.81,0:05:40.31,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:41.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:50.16,Main,,0,0,0,,As I thought, it's blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.83,0:05:56.87,Main,,0,0,0,,What kind of notes are these?\NI can't read them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:05:59.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? They're totally readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.38,0:06:00.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Not readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.33,0:06:01.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:02.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Not readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:03.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:04.55,Main,,0,0,0,,It's readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:07.42,Main,,0,0,0,,See? Shun says they're readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:14.47,Main,,0,0,0,,It's readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.03,0:06:33.16,Main,,0,0,0,,B-Big brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.87,0:06:39.21,Main,,0,0,0,,The basement room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.87,0:06:42.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.38,0:06:43.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.38,0:06:51.43,Main,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.43,0:06:52.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.43,0:06:53.80,Main,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.43,0:06:58.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.89,0:07:02.90,Main,,0,0,0,,But why did it open now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.52,0:07:06.65,Main,,0,0,0,,It could be related to Mari's pendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:08.36,Main,,0,0,0,,What? My pendant?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:11.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. The mechanism started spinning, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.53,0:07:15.45,Main,,0,0,0,,I think it's still spinning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.45,0:07:19.79,Main,,0,0,0,,That reminds me... when I traveled\Nback to Mr. Gilbert's era,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.79,0:07:21.79,Main,,0,0,0,,it did the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.79,0:07:24.33,Main,,0,0,0,,What is that pendant?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:26.25,Main,,0,0,0,,I got it from my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.25,0:07:28.09,Main,,0,0,0,,From the doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.09,0:07:33.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if the book's readable now,\Nthe answer must be in there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.05,0:07:35.76,Main,,0,0,0,,But only the first part is readable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.76,0:07:38.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.56,0:07:42.81,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know. But I can\Nread the Gilbert page.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:47.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Last time, I was flipping\Nthrough this part...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.90,0:07:51.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.65,0:07:53.16,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.66,0:07:56.83,Main,,0,0,0,,He's the guy from our lesson today!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.87,0:08:02.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.92,0:08:04.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.75,0:08:11.13,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1752\N(What is Now) Philadelphia, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:16.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Peter, why the long face?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:18.14,Main,,0,0,0,,You're offending the girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.14,0:08:20.31,Main,,0,0,0,,How can you stand it, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:22.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Stand what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:24.35,Main,,0,0,0,,The way the church is acting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.31,0:08:30.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Exactly how would installing a\Nlightning rod be an affront to God?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.48,0:08:34.49,Main,,0,0,0,,The church is the tallest building in town.\NIf they hadn't refused to install it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:37.99,Main,,0,0,0,,we could have avoided some of\Nthe damage from the lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.99,0:08:41.70,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess they just don't trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:43.50,Main,,0,0,0,,How can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:45.67,Main,,0,0,0,,You're a fantastic scientist!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.67,0:08:48.71,Main,,0,0,0,,And an amazing statesman, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.71,0:08:51.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, you flatter me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:53.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Look, listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:57.59,Main,,0,0,0,,That sounded close...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.90,0:09:13.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:16.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother... look!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.32,0:09:17.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:19.87,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.71,0:09:34.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:36.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:38.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.43,0:09:40.64,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm John.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.64,0:09:41.93,Main,,0,0,0,,John?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:44.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.73,0:09:48.56,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.73,0:09:53.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.57,0:09:56.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? The master's laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:09:58.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.53,0:10:03.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Dr. Benjamin Franklin. Do you know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.08,0:10:05.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Benjamin Franklin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:11.34,Main,,0,0,0,,I see... I'm back in time again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.59,0:10:16.30,Main,,0,0,0,,John! Sorry I'm late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:18.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's really coming down out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:19.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.93,0:10:21.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.93,0:10:26.14,Main,,0,0,0,,I've discovered a beautiful girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.14,0:10:29.56,Main,,0,0,0,,A pleasure to meet you.\NI am Benjamin Franklin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.56,0:10:31.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? You?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.48,0:10:36.94,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Dazzled by my good looks?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:38.28,Main,,0,0,0,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:40.28,Main,,0,0,0,,No need to be shy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.28,0:10:41.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm not shy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.57,0:10:44.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe I'll show you\Nan interesting experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.45,0:10:47.12,Main,,0,0,0,,that'll unravel your heart a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:49.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you even listening to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:50.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:52.63,Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm getting ready for an experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.63,0:10:55.67,Main,,0,0,0,,so your confession of love\Nwill have to wait for later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:03.51,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a Leyden jar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.51,0:11:06.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Right now, if I bring this\Nmetal instrument near it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.85,0:11:10.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.73,0:11:12.90,Main,,0,0,0,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.81,0:11:19.36,Main,,0,0,0,,If I use a cotton rag to charge this\Nglass rod with static electricity...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:22.16,Main,,0,0,0,,...and transfer the electricity to the jar...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.66,0:11:28.50,Main,,0,0,0,,...and move the metal\Ninstrument close once again...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:34.88,Main,,0,0,0,,...the electric charge stored up in\Nthe Leyden jar flew into the rod!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.88,0:11:38.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, if you sharpen the tips of the rod,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.92,0:11:42.38,Main,,0,0,0,,it can receive electricity\Nacross an even greater distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.38,0:11:44.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:46.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Well? Falling in love all over again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:50.85,Main,,0,0,0,,A-Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:11:59.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.11,0:12:03.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Something smells good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:04.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.70,0:12:06.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Join me, Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:07.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:11.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.25,0:12:13.58,Main,,0,0,0,,That was delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:15.75,Main,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.75,0:12:19.55,Main,,0,0,0,,I hope this 18th century\Ncoffee agrees with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.55,0:12:20.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.38,0:12:22.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.34,0:12:24.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you believed\Nmy story from last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.97,0:12:27.39,Main,,0,0,0,,No, I find it dubious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:31.39,Main,,0,0,0,,It's hard to take it on faith that\Nyou're from the future, Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.39,0:12:34.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, it's Mari, not Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.19,0:12:37.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Marie sounds nicer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.23,0:12:39.19,Main,,0,0,0,,N-Nicer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:42.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? John...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.28,0:12:44.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Doesn't he go to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:47.24,Main,,0,0,0,,School? John is a slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.24,0:12:48.24,Main,,0,0,0,,A slave?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.24,0:12:52.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you saying... there are no\Nslaves where you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.87,0:12:54.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:57.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Then who does your cleaning and your laundry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:12:59.88,Main,,0,0,0,,We have vacuums and laundry machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.88,0:13:01.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Vacuums?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.30,0:13:03.26,Main,,0,0,0,,What are those?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.26,0:13:05.18,Main,,0,0,0,,What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.18,0:13:07.93,Main,,0,0,0,,They're machines that run on electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.93,0:13:12.06,Main,,0,0,0,,The newest ones will move around\Nyour room at scheduled times
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.06,0:13:14.52,Main,,0,0,0,,and sweep up the dust\Non the floor on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:17.77,Main,,0,0,0,,With laundry machines, you just put\Nthe dirty stuff in and press a switch,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.77,0:13:20.69,Main,,0,0,0,,and it does everything, from\Nwashing to drying, by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.69,0:13:22.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow, all with electricity?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:23.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:25.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.95,0:13:28.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Is it really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.37,0:13:33.66,Main,,0,0,0,,But here, cleaning and laundry\Nare done by slaves, like John.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.33,0:13:40.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, speaking of which, how did\Nyou get here from the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:42.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.67,0:13:46.84,Main,,0,0,0,,...I read a page about you\Nin a mysterious book.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:49.85,Main,,0,0,0,,What? Are they writing books about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.85,0:13:51.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.05,0:13:52.47,Main,,0,0,0,,That's incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.47,0:13:56.10,Main,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's over 250 years\Ninto the future, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:13:58.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.15,0:14:01.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.11,0:14:03.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.19,0:14:05.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we head out on a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.74,0:14:07.11,Main,,0,0,0,,D-Date?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.86,0:14:10.32,Main,,0,0,0,,You're searching for your papa, right, Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:11.74,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.92,0:14:22.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Won't you at least take my arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.00,0:14:23.46,Main,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.18,0:14:33.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy. Looks like it's going to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:41.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Rain, rain, go away! Come again on Saturday!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.15,0:14:42.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Good, Laura!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:44.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:53.24,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems no one knew\Nanything about your papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:54.70,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.70,0:14:56.41,Main,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.41,0:14:58.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, no... it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.37,0:15:00.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Please don't apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.21,0:15:03.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Really, I should be thanking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:05.38,Main,,0,0,0,,You're a charming girl, Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.38,0:15:07.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.63,0:15:10.55,Main,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tease me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:17.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:19.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Why don't we go look for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.90,0:15:24.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Put the fire out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:26.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Get the injured into the church!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.57,0:15:28.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Dear! Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.23,0:15:30.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Please, speak to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:32.57,Main,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.57,0:15:34.91,Main,,0,0,0,,The cause of the lightning strike earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:36.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:37.74,Main,,0,0,0,,John!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.54,0:15:50.67,Main,,0,0,0,,John... You went over there to shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:53.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Why does she care so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.43,0:15:54.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:59.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Let us pray that God's wrath calms quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.72,0:16:01.18,Main,,0,0,0,,We must not rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:03.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Come, rise up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.81,0:16:08.44,Main,,0,0,0,,No, John! You have to rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.44,0:16:09.78,Main,,0,0,0,,I need to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.78,0:16:11.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:16.49,Main,,0,0,0,,They've decided the lightning\Nis the wrath of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.49,0:16:19.70,Main,,0,0,0,,In the name of the Father,\Nthe Son, and the Holy Ghost,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.70,0:16:20.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.79,0:16:24.54,Main,,0,0,0,,In the name of the Father,\Nthe Son, and the Holy Ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.54,0:16:26.79,Main,,0,0,0,,--Amen.\N--The Father, the Son...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.79,0:16:29.67,Main,,0,0,0,,...and the Holy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.67,0:16:33.59,Main,,0,0,0,,John! Forget that! I need to cool your burns!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:37.72,Main,,0,0,0,,But God... will be angry...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.72,0:16:40.64,Main,,0,0,0,,You're wrong! That's not true, John!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.64,0:16:47.56,Main,,0,0,0,,God. Please forgive our many sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:51.57,Main,,0,0,0,,God... please forgive... our many...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.32,0:16:56.32,Main,,0,0,0,,What sins, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.32,0:16:57.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:17:02.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that John and the people\Nhere have done something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.62,0:17:05.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.79,0:17:09.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Lightning isn't the wrath of God!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.00,0:17:10.55,Main,,0,0,0,,It's just electricity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.55,0:17:13.38,Main,,0,0,0,,You people again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:17.18,Main,,0,0,0,,If it's about your lightning rod,\NI already refused to put it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.01,0:17:19.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.64,0:17:23.02,Main,,0,0,0,,It would prevent damage\Nfrom lightning strikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.02,0:17:26.31,Main,,0,0,0,,It would let the lightning's\Nelectricity pass safely by!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:32.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Franklin, tell them! Tell them\Nthat lightning is electricity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.11,0:17:33.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:35.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.20,0:17:39.62,Main,,0,0,0,,But well done is better than well said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:41.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.08,0:17:44.79,Main,,0,0,0,,I will prove to you that\Nlightning is electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:46.58,Main,,0,0,0,,If I succeed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:51.21,Main,,0,0,0,,will you consider installing\Na lightning rod on the church?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.21,0:17:52.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:54.55,Main,,0,0,0,,You're safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.55,0:17:57.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Peter! Prepare a kite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.13,0:17:59.39,Main,,0,0,0,,What? A kite?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.39,0:18:01.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Doctor. You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.56,0:18:08.14,Main,,0,0,0,,There's someone here I have to convince.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.14,0:18:10.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Lightning is electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:13.23,Main,,0,0,0,,The power of science can\Nreduce the damage it causes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:17.70,Main,,0,0,0,,John...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:20.41,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll prove it to you, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:21.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.74,0:18:26.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... that kite for your experiment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:28.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Could I make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.21,0:18:35.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:38.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Th-That's a kite?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:40.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes! It's called a yakko dako!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:45.68,Main,,0,0,0,,I once won an award for a kite\NI made over winter break, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.68,0:18:46.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Everything ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.93,0:18:49.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.48,0:18:50.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Then it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.81,0:18:53.02,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.02,0:18:55.19,Main,,0,0,0,,A kite, she claims.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:03.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Excellent. Very artistic!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.38,0:19:23.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Forgive the wait, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.93,0:19:26.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Right now, this jar is\Ncompletely unremarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.51,0:19:31.69,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to charge it with the essence of\Nlightning, and show you a mini lightning bolt!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.69,0:19:34.27,Main,,0,0,0,,What is the essence of lightning?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.27,0:19:36.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the question, my lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:38.53,Main,,0,0,0,,The essence of lightning
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.53,0:19:42.24,Main,,0,0,0,,is the electricity stored up\Nin those thunderclouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:46.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to use the key attached to\Nthe string of this kite to draw it in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.62,0:19:49.25,Main,,0,0,0,,and store it inside this jar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.12,0:19:53.12,Main,,0,0,0,,It's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:08.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Now the essence of lightning\Nis stored in this bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.68,0:20:10.52,Main,,0,0,0,,It's time to unleash it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.52,0:20:12.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Unleash it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.23,0:20:14.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes! The real show is just about to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.69,0:20:18.61,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll show you a little lightning strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:23.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I hope this proves to him that lightning\Nis a scientific phenomenon, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.79,0:20:31.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Please, go well!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.96,0:20:35.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? W-Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:41.63,Main,,0,0,0,,He did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:45.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you understand now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.35,0:20:51.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:55.31,Main,,0,0,0,,The future... It's amazing, Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.73,0:21:00.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:03.03,Main,,0,0,0,,That hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.03,0:21:04.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.62,0:21:14.25,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.01,0:21:25.59,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:27.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.22,0:21:28.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.51,0:21:30.76,Main,,0,0,0,,"The father of American independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:33.31,Main,,0,0,0,,He spoke up for the abolition of slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.31,0:21:36.19,Main,,0,0,0,,And he's also famous for his\Nexperiments with lightning."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:39.36,Main,,0,0,0,,So you were researching\Nabout Benjamin Franklin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:40.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.23,0:21:43.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow. And he's on the 100 dollar bill, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.40,0:21:46.70,Main,,0,0,0,,But is this really Mr. Franklin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.70,0:21:48.91,Main,,0,0,0,,He was a little handsomer when I saw him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.91,0:21:50.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.12,0:21:53.54,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.54,0:21:56.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I was translating Mr. Franklin's famous phrases.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.37,0:21:58.46,Main,,0,0,0,,It's useful for studying English.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.46,0:22:01.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Mari, you study English?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.59,0:22:03.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.51,0:22:08.18,Main,,0,0,0,,I never liked studying before...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.76,0:22:13.85,Main,,0,0,0,,...but I guess being able\Nto learn things really is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.85,0:22:16.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay! It's so wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.48,0:22:19.56,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll do my best for your support.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.32,0:22:26.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka... Please say it in Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.82,0:22:29.95,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode:\NVolta on the Battlefield"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.04,0:24:00.50,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.50,0:24:02.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.92,0:24:08.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Franklin said that lightning was\Nreally electricity, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.42,0:24:11.63,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to charge it with\Nthe essence of lightning,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.63,0:24:14.18,Main,,0,0,0,,and show you a mini lightning bolt!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.06,0:24:22.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Now let's try the same thing\Nwith modern technology!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.02,0:24:23.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:26.02,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.02,0:24:27.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.61,0:24:32.61,Main,,0,0,0,,If we move this little ball of metal\Ntowards this big ball of metal...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.86,0:24:36.32,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.32,0:24:37.49,Main,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.49,0:24:40.79,Main,,0,0,0,,It's just like Mr. Franklin's\Nexperiment with his Leyden jar!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.37,0:24:45.46,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a Van der Graaf Generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.46,0:24:47.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Van der Graaf?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.59,0:24:48.71,Main,,0,0,0,,"Static Electricity"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.71,0:24:52.30,Main,,0,0,0,,It uses the friction between\Ntwo rollers powered by a motor\N"Static Electricity"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.30,0:24:57.60,Main,,0,0,0,,and a rubber belt to create\Nand store up static electricity.\N"Static Electricity"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.60,0:24:57.85,Main,,0,0,0,,and a rubber belt to create\Nand store up static electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.72,0:25:02.27,Main,,0,0,0,,It's making artificial lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.27,0:25:03.98,Main,,0,0,0,,But static electricity...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.98,0:25:08.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that the same as the\Nelectricity we use every day?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.02,0:25:10.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's test it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.73,0:25:15.57,Main,,0,0,0,,If we channel it through\Na fluorescent light...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.70,0:25:17.78,Main,,0,0,0,,It lit up!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.78,0:25:19.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow! Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.49,0:25:22.50,Main,,0,0,0,,The static electricity stored\Nup in that metal sphere
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.50,0:25:25.16,Main,,0,0,0,,can even light up a fluorescent light bulb!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.16,0:25:26.33,Main,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.33,0:25:28.83,Main,,0,0,0,,So lightning really is electricity!
